        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-17T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-17T15:00:00-05:00" n="628" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d628">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00B/10–1749: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-17T15:00:00-05:00">October 17, 1949—3 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>718. Dept desires clarification composition of CCP<note n="12" xml:id="d628fn12">Chinese Communist Party.</note> Politburo. Presently accepts fol[lowing] as
                    correct: Mao Tse-tung, Chu Te, Chou En-lai, Liu Shao-chi, Jen Pi-shih, Kao Kang,
                    Peng Chen, Chen Yun, Peng Te-huai, Lin Tsu-han, Tung Pi-wu, Kang Sheng. Various
                    sources also list Wang Chia-hsiang, Chen Shao-yu, Chang Wen-tien, Li Fu-chun, Li
                    Wei-han, Wu Liang-ping. Pls comment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
